    "message_1": "Suppose we have the following data: (0, 1), (1, 8), (2, 27), (3, 64), (4, 125). \n\nUsing Lagrange polynomials, find the value of the function at x = 2.5.",
    "message_2": "To find the value of the function at x = 2.5 using Lagrange polynomials, we will use the following formula:\n\nL(x) = f(x0) * L0(x) + f(x1) * L1(x) + f(x2) * L2(x) + f(x3) * L3(x) + f(x4) * L4(x)\n\nwhere Lk(x) = Π((x - xi) / (xk - xi)) for i = 0, 1, 2, 3, 4 and i ≠ k.\n\nGiven data points: (0, 1), (1, 8), (2, 27), (3, 64), (4, 125)\n\nL0(x) = ((x - 1) * (x - 2) * (x - 3) * (x - 4)) / ((0 - 1) * (0 - 2) * (0 - 3) * (0 - 4))\nL1(x) = ((x - 0) * (x - 2) * (x - 3) * (x - 4)) / ((1 - 0) * (1 - 2) * (1 - 3) * (1 - 4))\nL2(x) = ((x - 0) * (x - 1) * (x - 3) * (x - 4)) / ((2 - 0) * (2 - 1) * (2 - 3) * (2 - 4))\nL3(x) = ((x - 0) * (x - 1) * (x - 2) * (x - 4)) / ((3 - 0) * (3 - 1) * (3 - 2) * (3 - 4))\nL4(x) = ((x - 0) * (x - 1) * (x - 2) * (x - 3)) / ((4 - 0) * (4 - 1) * (4 - 2) * (4 - 3))\n\nNow, we will substitute x = 2.5 into the Lagrange polynomials:\n\nL(2.5) = 1 * L0(2.5) + 8 * L1(2.5) + 27 * L2(2.5) + 64 * L3(2.5) + 125 * L4(2.5)\n\nAfter calculating the values of L0(2.5), L1(2.5), L2(2.5), L3(2.5), and L4(2.5), we get:\n\nL(2.5) = 1 * (-0.375) + 8 * 1.5 + 27 * (-0.125) + 64 * 0.5 + 125 * (-0.5)\nL(2.5) = -0.375 + 12 - 3.375 + 32 - 62.5\nL(2.5) = -22.25\n\nSo, the value of the function at x = 2.5 using Lagrange polynomials is -22.25."
